# Blog post writing (eugenetheengineer.com)

When creating or editing a post in `_posts/`, complete **all** applicable steps in the same change — before merge.

## Slug

Derive from filename: `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` → `<slug>` (no date prefix).

Permalink: `/posts/<slug>/`

## Front matter (required)

- `title`, `date`, `description`, `tags`, `categories`, `author: eugene`
- `redirect_from` with legacy `/YYYY/MM/DD/<slug>/` paths
- `render_with_liquid: false` unless the post body uses Liquid

## Cluster assignment (automatic)

**Set exactly one primary cluster via `categories:`** — hub listing and "More in this series" cross-links update automatically on the scheduled build when `date` passes.

| Category | Hub page |
|----------|----------|
| PostgreSQL Performance | [/postgresql-performance-playbook/](/postgresql-performance-playbook/) |
| Billing & Fintech | [/billing-systems-for-rails-engineers/](/billing-systems-for-rails-engineers/) |
| Backend Engineering | [/backend-engineering/](/backend-engineering/) |
| Architecture | [/architecture/](/architecture/) |
| Engineering Leadership | [/engineering-leadership/](/engineering-leadership/) |
| Personal | No hub (intentional) |

No manual slug lists. Jekyll `site.categories` + daily cron (`0 10 * * *` UTC) publish future-dated posts and add them to the hub on that day.

### Optional curation (`_data/clusters.yml`)

Add or update entries only when you want curated **Start here**, **By problem**, **Tools**, or **Related** sections:

- `featured` — reading-order slugs with blurbs
- `problems` — symptom → post map
- `tools` / `related` — external tools or cross-cluster links

Full post lists are never hand-maintained in YAML.

### In-post links (recommended)

- Link to your cluster hub at least once
- Cross-link 2–3 peer posts in the body when editorially useful (widget links all peers automatically)

## Verify

```bash
ruby tools/audit_clusters.rb
bundle exec jekyll build
```

## Do not

- Link to future-dated posts from published posts unless intentional preview
- Hand-edit hub tab bodies — hubs render from `_layouts/cluster.html` + `_data/clusters.yml`
- Use `categories: [Personal]` for SEO pillar content
